  "texts": [
    "In TOOLGEN, we explore the utilization of three distinct code LLMs to encompass diverse model architectures and parameter scales.",
    "These code LLMs demonstrate impressive performance in code generation and have found extensive utilization in prior studies [4], [5], [12], [33], [39] for fine-tuning and evaluation.• CodeGPT: CodeGPT [33] falls into the category of decoder-only models.",
    "It undergoes pre-training on a Python corpus sourced from the CodeSearchNet dataset [40], comprising 1.1 million Python functions.",
    "For our purposes, we adopt the pre-trained CodeGPTsmall versionfoot_0, which encompasses 124 million model parameters.",
    "• CodeT5: CodeT5 [4] belongs to the encoder-decoder model category and is similarly pre-trained on the Python corpus from the CodeSearchNet dataset."
  ],
